description: Gets a list of all KMS keys in the caller's Amazon Web Services account and Region. Cross-account use: No. You cannot perform this operation on a KMS key in a different Amazon Web Services account. Required permissions: kms:ListKeys (IAM policy) Eventual consistency: The KMS API follows an eventual consistency model. For more information, see KMS eventual consistency.

parameters.name: Limit
parameters.description: Use this parameter to specify the maximum number of items to return. When this value is present, KMS does not return more than the specified number of items, but it might return fewer. This value is optional. If you include a value, it must be between 1 and 1000, inclusive. If you do not include a value, it defaults to 100.

nested_items.name: NextMarker
nested_items.description: When Truncated is true, this element is present and contains the value to use for the Marker parameter in a subsequent request.

nested_items.name: Truncated
nested_items.description: A flag that indicates whether there are more items in the list. When this value is true, the list in this response is truncated. To get more items, pass the value of the NextMarker element in this response to the Marker parameter in a subsequent request.
